{"source":"user-event","type":"click","text":"C\n    \n      Modular Monolith + Domain Events\n      Option A's structure with an internal event bus for module communication\n      \n        ── server/\n        \n          \n            modules/ ← Same as Option A\n          \n          \n            events/ ← Internal event bus (EventEmitter or pg LISTEN/NOTIFY)\n            deal.stage.changed → triggers email, Procore sync, task creation\n            contact.created → triggers dedup check, touchpoint alert\n            email.received → triggers task creation, deal logging\n            deal.won → triggers Procore project creation\n          \n        \n        ── worker/ & client/ & shared/\n        Same as Option A\n      \n      \n        Pros\n          Same simplicity as Option A — single server, same folder structure\n          Event bus decouples modules — deal module doesn't call email module directly\n          Easy to trace \"what happens when X\" — check event handlers\n          Natural path to microservices later — events become message queue topics\n          Perfect for CRM workflows (deal won → chain of automated actions)\n        \n        Cons\n          Slightly more upfront design than pure Option A\n          Event ordering and error handling need thought\n          Can be over-engineered if events are used for everything","choice":"c","id":null,"timestamp":1775065757400}
